dcterms:creator: A. Cohan
B. Desmet
A. Yates
L. Soldaini
S. MacAvaney
N. Goharian
dcterms:description: A large dataset of social media posts from users with nine mental health conditions corresponding to branches in the DSM-5. User-level MHC labels were obtained through carefully designed distantly supervised labeling processes based on diagnosis pattern matching.
dcterms:title: Self-Reported Mental Health Diagnoses (SMHD)

dcterms:creator: E. Turcan
K. McKeown
dcterms:description: A dataset of lengthy social media posts from subreddits in five domains that include stressful and non-stressful text. Binary labels for stressful and non-stressful posts were obtained from aggregated ratings of five crowdsourced human annotators.
dcterms:title: Dreaddit

dcterms:creator: G. Gkotsis
A. Oellrich
S. Velupillai
M. Liakata
T. J. P. Hubbard
R. J. B. Dobson
R. Dutta
dcterms:description: A dataset of 458,240 posts from mental health related subreddits paired with a control set of approximately matched size. The posts were grouped into 11 mental health condition themes based on a combination of manual assessment and automated topic detection.
dcterms:title: Gkotsis et al. Dataset

dcterms:creator: A. Murarka
B. Radhakrishnan
S. Ravichandran
dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of Reddit posts with labels for five mental health conditions. The model was trained using RoBERTa to build multiclass models for identifying these conditions.
dcterms:title: Murarka et al. Dataset
